defaultAlun defaultCairnsdefault:default I know what they said; I want to know what you think.  
defaultProfessor Shute:default I think that they were right.  Unless, as I was indicating earlier, the leadership makes it clear that crime recording is a key, central, core function for the police, and unless those messages go out strong, clear and loud, and 
defaultare 
defaultregularly transmitted, it will be inevitable that you will find regression from officers lower down in the hierarchy.  Leadership, as with any organisation, is absolutely key.  Structures, processes and systems are really important too, as well as the right leadership messages.  I know that you are going to come to those issues in a moment, but Force Crime Registrars and the governance structures matter.  In my view, there are improvements that can be made there
