defaultJeff Farrardefault: We have had targets for some time, but I was in the service back in the late 1980s and 1990s, where we had limited performance management; we had no targets.  If you had asked me the questions you are asking me today then, it would not have been as good as it is now.  However, I really do think there is a place for performance management in the service.  My own personal view: is there a place for targets?  I think they can drive the wrong behaviour.  There are not any targets in my own particular force.  It is varied across the country.  If you have a personal target
